FBIS3-7370 "dreas059_q_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 AUSTRALASIA Australia Government Announces Cabinet Reshuffle 25 Mar BK2503083194 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 25 Mar 94 BK2503083194 Melbourne Radio Australia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Australia's Prime Minister Paul Keating has elevated a junior left-wing minister to cabinet as well as giving Dr. Carmen Laurence the rapid promotion expected in his latest ministerial changes. In a wider than anticipated reshuffle, science has had a major elevation into cabinet, and Linda Mottram reports the deputy prime minister, Brian Howe, has defied his critics to take on a significant new area. [Begin Mottram recording] Carmen Laurence, picked as a future labor leader, is in cabinet as health and human services minister less than a week after taking up her new seat in federal parliament. A second edition to the front bench is Queensland's right-winger, Con Sciacca, becoming veteran affairs minister. A third is former minister, Gary Punch, taking on defense, science, and personnel. Rewarded is left-winger, John Faulkner, who is elevated to cabinet as environment minister; another left-winger, the deputy prime minister, Brian Howe, as regional development to his housing responsibility. Chris Schacht moves to troubled science arm of his small business and customs portfolio. Science is elevated to cabinet under Industry Minister Peter Cook. Other changes cover administrative services, special ministerial state, and some parliamentary secretaries. [end recording]
